# Cursor Adapter

This is the reference copy of the Cursor rule. The **working version** lives at `.cursor/rules/think-in-html.mdc`.

## How it works

Cursor loads rules from `.cursor/rules/` in your project root. When the rule's description matches the user's intent (e.g., "explain this code interactively"), Cursor activates it.

## Manual installation (if not using install.sh)

1. Copy the `core/` folder into your project (e.g., as `think-in-html/core/`)
2. Copy `.cursor/rules/think-in-html.mdc` into your project's `.cursor/rules/`
3. Update paths inside the rule file if you placed `core/` in a subdirectory

## Usage

In Cursor chat, ask:
- "Use think-in-html to explain this file"
- "Generate an interactive HTML walkthrough of src/auth/"
- "Create a Think-In-HTML explainer for this module"
